<problem display_name="Décomposition LU : problème 13" markdown="null" max_attempts="1" showanswer="attempted" weight="2.0">
  <p>Soit \(A=\left(
  \begin{matrix}
  1 &amp; 4 &amp; -1 \\
  2 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
  1 &amp; -5 &amp; 2 \\
  \end{matrix}
  \right)
  \) et \(U=L_{32}(-\frac{9}{8})L_{31}(-1)L_{21}(-2)A\) une forme échelonnée.</p>
  <p>Alors</p>
  <multiplechoiceresponse>
    <choicegroup label="Alors" type="MultipleChoice">
      <choice correct="false">\(U=
      \left(
      \begin{matrix}
      1 &amp; 4 &amp; -1 \\
      0 &amp; 8 &amp; -5 \\
      0 &amp; 0 &amp; -\frac{21}{8} \\
      \end{matrix}
    \right)\).</choice>
      <choice correct="true">\(U=
      \left(
    \begin{matrix}
      1 &amp; 4 &amp; -1 \\
      0 &amp; -8 &amp; 5 \\
      0 &amp; 0 &amp; -\frac{21}{8} \\
     \end{matrix}
      \right)\).</choice>
      <choice correct="false">\(U=
      \left(
      \begin{matrix}
      1 &amp; 4 &amp; -1 \\
      0 &amp; -8 &amp; 5 \\
      0 &amp; 0 &amp; \frac{21}{8} \\
      \end{matrix}
    \right)\).</choice>
    </choicegroup>
  </multiplechoiceresponse>
  <solution>
    <div class="detailed-solution">
      <p>Explication</p>
      <p>On applique les opérations élémentaires mentionnées à la matrice \(A\), en commençant depuis la droite.</p>
      <p> Soient \(A'=L_{21}(-2)A\) et \(A''=L_{31}(-1)A'\). On a </p>
      <p> \(A= \left(\begin{matrix} 1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 2-2\cdot 1 &amp;0-2\cdot 4 &amp; 3-2 \cdot(-1)\\
    1 &amp; -5 &amp; 2
    \end{matrix} \right) = \left(\begin{matrix}  1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 0 &amp;-8 &amp; 5\\
    1 &amp; -5 &amp; 2\end{matrix}\right).\)</p>
      <p> \(\textrm{et} \quad A''=\left(\begin{matrix} 1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 0 &amp;-8 &amp; 5\\
    1-1\cdot 1 &amp; -5-1\cdot 4 &amp; 2-1\cdot (-1)  \end{matrix} \right) = \left(\begin{matrix}
    1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 0 &amp;-8 &amp; 5\\
    0 &amp; -9 &amp; 3
    \end{matrix}\right).\)</p>
      <p> Finalement, soit \(A'''=L_{32}(-9/8)A''\). Alors \(U=A'''\) et </p>
      <p> \(U= \left(\begin{matrix}
    1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 0 &amp;-8 &amp; 5\\
    0-\frac{9}{8} \cdot 0 &amp; -9-\frac 98 \cdot (-8) &amp; 3-\frac{9}{8}\cdot 5
    \end{matrix}\right)=  \left(\begin{matrix}
    1 &amp; 4 &amp;-1\\ 0 &amp;-8 &amp; 5\\
    0 &amp; 0 &amp; -21/8
    \end{matrix}\right).\)</p>
    </div>
  </solution>
</problem>
